	<h3>Notes</h3>
	<p class="text-warning">It's hard to visualize YAC for running backs, because the stats produced by various outlets always shows a much higher YAC than the number of receptions. I'm not entirely sure why this is, but it means that this visualization shows all running back yards as consisting entirely of YAC.</p>
	<p class="text-warning">The data is from receiving stats, so if a player was traded half-way through a season they are not included (the data would mark their team as GB/BUF, for example, making it impossible to tell where the yards were produced.</p>

